        {
            "name": "Tiger",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [],
            "text": "Tigers are solitary and territorial hunters, using their striped hides to blend into the forests and jungles they call home and preferring to attack with surprise.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Animal</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"10\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Nature</a></u>)</b>: DC 19",
            "source": {
                "name": "Bestiary",
                "link": {
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                },
                "page": 53
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Cat",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Cat Locations",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "Leopards are exceptionally\nadaptable, able to survive in any\ngrassland, forest, or jungle, and\neven the fringes of deserts.<br/>\nLions live in grassy plains\nand savannas, although species\nadapted for temperate environs\nthat dwell in mountains exist as\nwell. Male mountain lions lack\nthe mane of their somewhat\nlarger grassland-dwelling kin,\nbut are no less dangerous.<br/>\nWhile tigers are most common\nin forests, they also inhabit\ngrasslands and savannas as long\nas vegetation is dense, and their\ndens are often found in caves.<br/>\nSmilodons live in wooded\nand grassland areas.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Bestiary",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                        },
                        "page": 52
                    },
                    "subtype": "locations",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Locations",
                    "image": "Sidebar_3_Locations.png"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Domesticating Big Cats",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "While it\u2019s common practice to keep\na house cat in the home to ward\noff unwanted rodents, keeping\na big cat for a pet is a different\nmatter entirely. Nevertheless,\nup-and-coming merchant lords,\nimpetuous princes and princesses,\nand status-obsessed nobles\nhave tried to do just that, often\nresulting only in terrified house\nstaff and ruined upholstery. Many\namong the idle rich will gladly pay\nfor the services of an unscrupulous\ndruid or ranger who promises to\nhelp them achieve their dreams\nof an oversized feline friend, but\nthe dire risks of such an endeavor\nare enough to dissuade even the\ngreediest would-be animal trainers\nfrom even attempting the feat.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Bestiary",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                        },
                        "page": 52
                    },
                    "subtype": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Few predators of the natural world can match the cat\u2019s talent for stalking and stealth.",
            "source": {
                "name": "Bestiary",
                "link": {
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                },
                "page": 52
